
'''* Book: A Theology of the Built Environment: Justice, Empowerment, Redemption.By T. J. Gorringe. New York, Cambridge University Press, 2002'''


=Description=

"In this book, Tim Gorringe, Professor of Theological Studies at the University of Exeter, addresses what he regards as an issue hitherto neglected within theological ethics. In stating that "what is called for is a theology of the built environment," Gorringe identifies two major undertakings: first, to establish why the built environment might be of theological importance; second, to begin to elaborate the substance of such a theology. He achieves both objectives."
(http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3664/is_200304/ai_n9185603/)


